· Dynamic re-optimization to adapt circuits to real-time calibration changes, ensuring optimality at execution time.
· Extensive empirical evaluation on benchmarks including VQE, QAOA, and QASMBench, with comparisons to state-of-the-art compilers on both noisy simulators and real IBM Quantum hardware.
· Open-source release of the discovered rule database, trained policy weights, and full benchmark results.

