Chapter 3: Related Work

Quantum circuit optimization has been studied extensively, with approaches ranging from hand-crafted rule-based systems to AI-driven methods. This chapter reviews the state of the art and positions our contribution.

3.1 Symbolic and Verified Compilers

3.1.1 PyZX

PyZX [3] is a Python library for automated reasoning with ZX-calculus. It implements a large set of rewrite rules and can significantly reduce T-count and CNOT count in Clifford+T circuits. PyZX is purely symbolic and does not incorporate hardware noise or AI guidance.

3.1.2 VOQC

VOQC [4,20] is a verified optimizer for quantum circuits implemented in the Coq proof assistant. It provides hand-crafted, correctness-proven rewrite rules. While it offers strong guarantees, its rule set is fixed and human-designed.

3.1.3 Giallar

Giallar [5] is a push-button verification tool for Qiskit transformation passes. It verifies that a given pass preserves unitary equivalence, but does not discover new passes.

3.2 AI-Driven Compilers

3.2.1 OrQstrator

OrQstrator [1] uses deep reinforcement learning to orchestrate multiple existing circuit rewriters and resynthesis tools. It selects sequences of passes to minimize a cost metric, but it does not discover new rewrite rules; it merely combines existing ones.

3.2.2 Agent-Q

Agent-Q [2] fine-tunes large language models to generate quantum circuits for specific applications (e.g., QAOA ansätze). It focuses on circuit generation rather than optimization, and does not verify equivalence.

3.2.3 Other ML Approaches

Reinforcement learning has been applied to quantum circuit optimization directly [6,7], but these typically operate on a fixed gate set and learn to reorder or replace gates without symbolic rule discovery.

3.3 Comparative Analysis

Approach Symbolic Guarantee AI/ML Component Noise-Aware? Verified?
PyZX ZX rewriting No (manual rules) No No
VOQC Verified in Coq No (hand-crafted) No Yes
Giallar Verified passes No (uses Qiskit) No Push-button
OrQstrator Orchestration DRL over rewriters No No
Agent-Q No (generation) Fine-tuned LLM No No
