3.4 The Gap in the Literature

None of the existing systems combine the following key elements:

· Automatic discovery of novel symbolic rewrite rules beyond those known to human experts.
· Formal verification of discovered rules to guarantee correctness.
· Hardware-aware search that directly optimizes for device-specific noise and connectivity.
· Integration with a powerful graphical representation (ZX-calculus) that makes many optimizations natural.

This dissertation fills that gap by proposing a neuro-symbolic framework where an LLM proposes candidate rules, a verifier checks them, and an RL agent learns to apply them optimally under a realistic hardware cost model.

