Appendix F: Proof of Equivalence Preservation Under Composition

Theorem: If each rewrite rule T_i satisfies U(T_i(C)) = U(C) for any circuit C to which it applies, then any sequence of such rules T_{i_m} \circ \cdots \circ T_{i_1} applied to an initial circuit C_0 yields a circuit C_m with U(C_m) = U(C_0).

Proof: By induction on m. Base case m=0 trivial. Assume U(C_{k}) = U(C_0). After applying T_{i_{k+1}} to C_k, we have U(C_{k+1}) = U(T_{i_{k+1}}(C_k)) = U(C_k) by the property of each rule. Hence U(C_{k+1}) = U(C_0). ∎

This theorem justifies the correctness of the entire optimization process as long as each applied rule is verified.

